WEBVTT

00:02.176 --> 00:03.836
It's amazing to me
that people move...

00:05.413 --> 00:07.643
...thousands of miles away
to another city.

00:07.814 --> 00:10.079
They think nothing of it.
They get on a plane.

00:10.251 --> 00:12.412
They live there now.

00:12.587 --> 00:14.578
Just a thousand miles...
I'm living over there.

00:14.756 --> 00:17.691
You know, pioneers... It took years
to cross the country.

00:17.859 --> 00:21.852
Now people will move thousands
of miles just for one season.

00:22.030 --> 00:24.055
I don't think any pioneers did that.

00:24.232 --> 00:26.530
"Yeah, it took us a decade
to get there...

00:26.701 --> 00:28.328
...and we stayed for the summer.

00:28.503 --> 00:31.233
It was nice. It had a pool.
The kids loved it.

00:31.406 --> 00:34.898
And then we left about 10 years ago,
and we just got back.

00:35.076 --> 00:37.067
We had a great summer.
It took us 20 years...

00:37.245 --> 00:39.236
...and now our lives are over."

00:44.519 --> 00:46.817
- Kramer was on Murphy Brown?
- Yeah.

00:46.988 --> 00:48.455
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

00:49.390 --> 00:51.290
Murphy Brown, the TV show?

00:51.459 --> 00:53.552
Come on, will you?

00:53.728 --> 00:58.722
Kramer was on Murphy Brown?
That son of a gun.

00:58.900 --> 01:01.198
- It's something, isn't it?
- With Candice Bergen.

01:01.369 --> 01:03.803
- I know.
- I've always liked her.

01:03.972 --> 01:05.438
Remember her
in Carnal Knowledge?

01:05.607 --> 01:08.132
- Sure.
- She show her breasts in that?

01:08.710 --> 01:10.940
She's not really the naked type.

01:11.346 --> 01:13.109
I can't believe I missed Kramer.

01:13.514 --> 01:15.209
He asked me to go with him.

01:15.617 --> 01:17.881
- He did?
- Yeah. I turned him down.

01:18.052 --> 01:20.885
- How come you didn't tell me?
- He asked me to keep it a secret.

01:21.055 --> 01:22.784
- You can never keep a secret.
- I know.

01:22.957 --> 01:25.983
This was like a record. My previous
record was when Jodi Hirsch...

01:26.160 --> 01:28.458
...asked me not to tell anybody
we slept together.

01:28.630 --> 01:31.030
I kept a lid on that
for about 28 seconds.

01:31.499 --> 01:34.161
- Well, you've come a long way.
- I've matured.

01:34.335 --> 01:36.200
The Tonight Show
called and they want me...

01:36.371 --> 01:39.534
...to do the show on the 28th.
They're giving me free tickets to L.A.

01:39.707 --> 01:41.436
You wanna go?

01:41.609 --> 01:43.076
A free ticket?

01:43.478 --> 01:45.673
Yeah. In fact, we could
track down Kramer.

01:45.847 --> 01:48.680
I always felt bad about the way
he left. That was a mess.

01:48.850 --> 01:51.375
I never should've taken back
those keys.

01:51.586 --> 01:54.146
- What about accommodations?
- All taken care of.

01:54.522 --> 01:56.888
Is there a meal allowance?

01:57.058 --> 01:58.889
What about seat assignments?

01:59.060 --> 02:01.756
Could I have the kosher meal?
I hear the kosher meal is good.

02:01.929 --> 02:05.023
And I need clothes.
I gotta get a haircut.

02:05.366 --> 02:07.766
And I have to refill
my allergy medication.

02:08.502 --> 02:10.835
Do I need a hat?
I need a hat, don't I?

02:11.172 --> 02:14.266
Could we do the Universal tour?
They have that Backdraft exhibit.

02:14.442 --> 02:15.966
Now, that looks very cool to me.

02:16.144 --> 02:20.604
See, my acting technique...
My personal acting technique...

02:20.982 --> 02:24.145
...is working with color.
Imagining color...

02:24.352 --> 02:27.048
...and then finding the emotional,
vibrational mood...

02:27.221 --> 02:28.745
...connected to the color.

02:29.323 --> 02:31.951
If you look through my scripts
you'll see that my lines...

02:32.126 --> 02:35.653
...have a special color.
So I don't memorize the language.

02:35.830 --> 02:40.164
I memorize color. This way, I can
go through red, yellow, green, blue.

02:40.334 --> 02:43.497
And you have a full palette
of emotions.

02:43.671 --> 02:45.104
Hey.

02:45.373 --> 02:47.705
Didn't I tell you to get out of here?

02:47.975 --> 02:49.203
- Did you?
- Let's go.

02:49.377 --> 02:51.311
- I was just...
- Yeah, you were just nothing.

02:51.479 --> 02:53.140
Come on, let's go.

02:53.414 --> 02:55.006
We'll talk about this
a little later.

02:55.183 --> 02:57.549
- Let's go.
- Are you an actor?

02:58.853 --> 03:00.753
See you, Mike!

